  "prompt": "When is a good time to switch from acoustic to electric guitar?",
  "response": "There's no definitive \"right\" time to switch from acoustic to electric guitar, but here are some good indicators:\n\n1. When you're comfortable with basic guitar skills\n- Know basic chords\n- Have decent strumming/picking technique\n- Understand music fundamentals\n\n2. Musical interests\n- Want to play rock, blues, metal, or jazz\n- Interested in different sound effects and tones\n- Want to experiment with distortion and solos\n\n3. Skill progression\n- Feel limited by acoustic guitar's sound\n- Want to explore different playing techniques\n- Ready to learn new skills like lead guitar\n\n4. Motivation factors\n- Have saved enough money for an electric guitar\n- Inspired by specific electric guitar players\n- Want to play in a band\n\n5. Personal preference\n- Simply enjoy electric guitar's sound\n- Find electric guitar more comfortable to play\n- Want more versatility in your playing\n\nPractical tips:\n- Start with a beginner-friendly electric guitar\n- Consider a practice amp\n- Take lessons or watch tutorials\n- Don't abandon your acoustic skills\n\nRemember, many guitarists play both acoustic and electric, so switching doesn't mean giving up one for the other.",
